This is a complex request because client-side HTML/JS **cannot directly talk to a Redis database** for security reasons. Browsers are not allowed to open raw TCP connections to databases; this would expose your database credentials to anyone visiting the site.

To make this functional, you normally need a **Backend API** (Node.js, Python, Go, etc.) to sit between the frontend and Redis.

However, **I can simulate the entire Redis experience perfectly within the browser** using `localStorage` and JavaScript classes. The interface will look and behave exactly like a real Redis management dashboard, but the data will be stored in your browser's local memory.

