Here is a complete, single-file solution containing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. I have designed this to be a fully functional "Spot the Difference" game.

To use this, save the code below as an `.html` file (e.g., `mrbean-game.html`) and open it in your web browser.

**Note:** Since I cannot generate real image files, I have used placeholder images via a placeholder service (`placehold.co`) and simulated the "differences" using invisible clickable zones overlaid on the images. In a real production environment, you would replace the image source URLs with actual Mr. Bean artwork.

